ive emotion allows theatre to dig deeper into what it means to be human.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAesthetics in literature. 0aAversion in literature. 0aDramaxHistory and criticism. 0aDramaxThemes, motives. 4aAbjection. 4aAesthetic Theory. 4aAesthetics. 4aDisgust. 4aHistory of Theatre. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aSarah Kane. 4aTheatre Studies. 4aTheatre. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aAbjection.  aAesthetic Theory.  aAesthetics.  aDisgust.  aHistory of Theatre.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aSarah Kane.  aTheatre Studies.  aTheatre.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2020z9783111025124oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z97831106896170 cprintz978383765210940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839452103?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839452103423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839452103/original  a978-3-11-068961-7  transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  